The issue is that you're mixing static (`/MT`) and dynamic (`/MD`) CRT libraries. Your code is compiled with `/MT` (static CRT), but some of the libraries you're linking against were likely compiled with `/MD` (dynamic CRT).

Here are the solutions:

## Solution 1: Use consistent CRT linking (Recommended)

**Option A: Use static CRT for everything (change to `/MT`)**
Make sure all libraries (libxml2s.lib, zlibstaticd.lib, libiconv.lib) are compiled with `/MT`:

```cmd
cl /MT /c test001.c /DXML_STATIC=1 /IC:\libxml2vc\include\libxml2
link test001.obj /LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib libxml2s.lib /LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib zlibstaticd.lib /LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib libiconv.lib bcrypt.lib /MANIFEST
```

**Option B: Use dynamic CRT for everything (change to `/MD`)**
```cmd
cl /MD /c test001.c /DXML_STATIC=1 /IC:\libxml2vc\include\libxml2
link test001.obj /LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib libxml2s.lib /LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib zlibstaticd.lib /LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib libiconv.lib bcrypt.lib /MANIFEST
```

## Solution 2: Use `/NODEFAULTLIB` selectively

If you can't recompile the libraries, you can exclude the conflicting default libraries:

```cmd
cl /MT /c test001.c /DXML_STATIC=1 /IC:\libxml2vc\include\libxml2
link test001.obj /LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib libxml2s.lib /LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib zlibstaticd.lib /LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib libiconv.lib bcrypt.lib /MANIFEST /NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRT /NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRTD
```

## Solution 3: Check library compilation settings

Verify how your libraries were compiled:
- Check if `libxml2s.lib` was compiled with `/MT` or `/MD`
- Check if `zlibstaticd.lib` was compiled with `/MT` or `/MD` 
- Check if `libiconv.lib` was compiled with `/MT` or `/MD`

You might need to rebuild some libraries with consistent CRT settings.

## Solution 4: Clean approach with proper library management

Create a response file to manage libraries more cleanly:

**link_options.txt:**
```
/LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib 
libxml2s.lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib 
zlibstaticd.lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib 
libiconv.lib 
bcrypt.lib 
/MANIFEST
/NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRT
/NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRTD
```

Then link with:
```cmd
link test001.obj @link_options.txt
```

**Most likely**, you need to ensure all your libraries are compiled with the same CRT option (`/MT` or `/MD`) as your main project. Try Solution 1 first.

